   <note>Affidavit of William Barrett of Charleston, Tennessee regarding the property of James P. Bates, who lost a great deal of property during the Civil War to Federal troops. Other documents include itemized account of lost property and the compensation that Bates is to be paid. Includes losses caused by the troops of Gen. Sherman, Col. Goode, Col Scott, Col Dibrell, Col Rucker, and Maj. Gen. Wheeler.</note>
